The paper deals with designing parallel algorithms and data structures for computational geometry problems, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also focuses on optimizing write efficiency, which is a key aspect of data structures (cs.DS) and parallel computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper introduces new techniques such as DAG tracing and α-labeling, which could be relevant to other areas such as programming languages and formal methods (cs.PL) and performance analysis (cs.PF).
